-- Virgin America Plans to Order 40 Airbus A320 Jets, Take Options on 20 More
-- Benjamin Purvis
-- 2010-07-22T09:37:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/virgin-america-plans-to-order-40-airbus-a320-jets-take-options-on-20-more.html

          
          
             Virgin America plans to order 40
Airbus A320 aircraft, with options for a further 20 planes, the
company said in a statement today.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Virgin America Inc. CEO David Cush pauses during a news conference on the fourth day of the Farnborough International Airshow. Photographer: Chris Ratcliffe/Bloomberg  
                           

     
